
[1]torpedo

   TORPE'DO, n. [L. from torpeo, to be numb.] The cramp fish or electric
   ray, Raia torpedo. This fish is usually taken in forty fathoms water,
   on the coast of France and England, and in the Mediterranean. A touch
   of this fish occasions a numbness in the limb, accompanied with an
   indescribable and painful sensation, and is really an electric shock.
   When dead,the fish loses its power of producing this sensation.
